# ChapterWriter Skill

## Purpose
Generates complete, high-quality textbook chapters in MDX format for the Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics interactive textbook. Produces production-ready content with pedagogical rigor, code examples, diagrams, and assessments.

## Inputs

```yaml
chapter_title:
  type: string
  description: "Title of the chapter (e.g., 'ROS 2 Publishers and Subscribers')"
  required: true

module_number:
  type: integer
  description: "Module number (1-4)"
  required: true

chapter_number:
  type: integer
  description: "Chapter number within module"
  required: true

audience_level:
  type: string
  enum: [beginner, intermediate, advanced]
  description: "Target audience level for depth and complexity"
  required: true

learning_outcomes:
  type: array<string>
  description: "3-5 learning outcomes students should achieve"
  example:
    - "Understand publisher-subscriber pattern in ROS 2"
    - "Create and run a custom ROS 2 node"
  required: true

key_concepts:
  type: array<string>
  description: "5-8 core concepts to cover"
  example:
    - "Topics", "Message types", "Quality of Service"
  required: false

code_language:
  type: string
  enum: [python, cpp, python+cpp]
  description: "Programming language for code examples"
  default: python
  required: false

include_external_refs:
  type: array<string>
  description: "External references (ROS 2 docs, papers, tutorials)"
  required: false
```

## Output

Complete MDX chapter file with the following structure:

```mdx
---
id: module-X-chapter-Y
title: Chapter Title
sidebar_label: Short Title
sidebar_position: Y
---

